{"description":"Flow computation can sometime try to create a message for exceptional symbolic value ({{exception is thrown.}} ) on a {{null}} tree which will result in NPE.\r\nThis can happen when exceptional symbolic value is not cleared on stack when entering finally block and parent of the first edge is empty block (can happen on more complex cfg with nested try-finally blocks). \r\n\r\n{code}\r\n void test(Object o, boolean b2) {\r\n    try {\r\n      try {\r\n        f(); \r\n      } finally {\r\n        if (b2) {\r\n          o \u003d null;\r\n          g();\r\n          o \u003d new Object();\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n      h();\r\n    } finally {\r\n      o.toString(); \r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"4.14"}